The mother of a baby girl has been shot dead and her child critically injured on Wednesday at Sweet Home Farm, an informal settlement in Philippi, Emergency Medical Services said.Spokesperson Robert Daniels said the woman was killed at about 9am.The six-month-old girl was rushed to Red Cross Children s Hospital in a critical but stable condition.Daniels said it was not a gang-related shooting: We believe there was a crime being committed, probably a robbery, and they were caught up in the crossfire .No arrests had been made. African News Agency